# Optional: Cloudflare Turnstile site key (must pair with API TURNSTILE_SECRET)
# When the player site and core API are on different origins, set the API base (no trailing slash).
# **Vercel / production:** you MUST set VITE_PLAYER_API_ORIGIN to your public Go API URL or login/register calls
# hit the static host and fail (HTTP 404 / "network"). Also add the player site URL to PLAYER_CORS_ORIGINS on core.
# Leave unset for local dev — Vite proxies /v1 and /health to DEV_API_PROXY (default http://127.0.0.1:9090).
# If the API runs on another port (e.g. PORT=9090 in services/core/.env), set:
# DEV_API_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:9090
# VITE_PLAYER_API_ORIGIN=https://api.example.com
#
# Bonus card images: staff uploads are stored as /v1/uploads/... . For production split hostings, set
# API_PUBLIC_BASE on the core API (see services/core/.env.example) so /v1/rewards/hub returns absolute
# image URLs; you can still set VITE_PLAYER_API_ORIGIN as a fallback for the same effect on relative paths.

# Same-site cookie auth: enable on core (PLAYER_COOKIE_AUTH) and set:
# VITE_PLAYER_CREDENTIALS=1
# (JWTs are not written to localStorage; leftover keys are cleared on load; session uses httpOnly cookies + CSRF double-submit.)
# When core sets PLAYER_COOKIE_OMIT_JSON_TOKENS=true, login/refresh omit tokens in JSON — keep VITE_PLAYER_CREDENTIALS=1.

# VITE_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY=

# Optional footer links on profile
# VITE_SUPPORT_URL=https://example.com/help
# VITE_RG_URL=https://example.com/responsible-gambling

# Admin console SPA origin (separate deploy). Used by optional cross-app helpers if enabled.
# VITE_ADMIN_APP_ORIGIN=http://localhost:5173

# --- Pigmo-style icon assets (optional) ---
# Shell icons: JSON map of slot → absolute URL. Slots: search, menu, message, bell, user, wallet.
# Capture URLs from DevTools → Network on https://pigmo.com/ (imagedelivery.net, .svg, .webp).
# Example (single line, minified):
# VITE_PIGMO_SHELL_ICONS={"search":"https://…/public","bell":"https://…/public"}
# VITE_PIGMO_SHELL_ICONS=
#
# Or point at a CF Images folder where you uploaded Pigmo glyphs as `{slot}.webp`:
# VITE_PIGMO_SHELL_ICON_BASE=https://imagedelivery.net/ACCOUNT_HASH/your-folder-id
#
# Use Pigmo Cloudflare “futures-icons” for BTC/ETH/SOL/DOGE wallet logos (see src/lib/pigmoIconAssets.ts).
# VITE_PIGMO_FUTURES_CRYPTO_ICONS=1
#
# Optional: map aggregator provider_system codes → Pigmo CF logo basename (slug). JSON object.
# Example: VITE_PROVIDER_LOGO_SLUGS_JSON={"qr":"quickspin","ae":"avatarux"}
# VITE_PROVIDER_LOGO_SLUGS_JSON=

# --- Fingerprint Pro (browser identification — public key only; never commit production keys to git)
# Dashboard → API keys → Public. Used by the JS agent to obtain visitorId + requestId sent to your API.
# VITE_FINGERPRINT_PUBLIC_KEY=
